snippet.textDisplay:
I have been there. It's so eerie. It's the buildings. The place looks like it should be inhabited; it feels like people will come out of their apartments. It's what we're used to when we see urban construction. But it's just silence. Nothing but silence in a fairly well preserved city. You never realise how much sound makes a place feel normal until there isn't any. When you realise that the last moments of civilisation was a frightful exodus, and you are standing in the soundless place that was once populated with normality, it really feels ghostly and uncanny.

Also, the Ukrainian people are some of the friendliest and most welcoming people I have ever had the chance to meet.
